        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-06-29T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-06-29T21:00:00-05:00" n="1413" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1413">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.9531/6–3049: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Tsingtao</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hawthorne</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tsingtao</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-06-30T10:00:00+08:00">June 30, 1949—10 a. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 10:16 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>302. Chinese military yesterday began removing from compound at 1 Kwangsi Road
                    Consulate General’s stocks of gas, kerosene and luboil (remytel 281, June
                    21).</p>
                <p>Sent Department 302, repeated Nanking 210, Shanghai 126.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hawthorne</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
